Character

utility class

- retrieve
    - valueOf(char c) returns Character of c
- compare
    - compareTo(char x, char y) compares two char values numerically
- convert
    - digit(char ch, int radix) returns numeric val of ch in the specified radix
    - toChars(int codePoint) returns char[] containing the UTF-16 representation of given char (Unicode code point)
    - toTitleCase(char ch)
    - toUpperCase(char ch)
    - toLowerCase(char ch)
    - toString(char c)
- check
    - isLetter(char ch)
    - isLetterOrDigit(char ch)
    - isDigit(char ch)
    - isAlphabetic(int codePoint)
    - isSpaceChar(char ch)
    - isLowerCase(char ch)
    - isUpperCase(char ch)
    - isTitleCase(char ch)
    - isWhiteSpace(char ch)
